&lt;p&gt;The world of industrial automation is undergoing a major transformation, driving manufacturers to challenge their assumptions of traditional design processes. Forced to abandon the “build it and tweak it” approach, they must begin to implement rigorous systems-design processes that accommodate the complexities of developing multi-disciplinary systems. In this new whitepaper Maplesoft explores why high-fidelity virtual prototypes, or Digital Twins, are at the core of this development process.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;ul&gt;
 &lt;li&gt;High-fidelity virtual prototypes, or Digital Twins, are at the core of implementing a rigorous systems-design processes that accommodate the complexities of developing multi-disciplinary systems.&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li&gt;Rapid task-planning and early problem detection are key benefits of integrating a Digital Twin of the machine design on a real-time platform.&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li&gt;A virtual machine can be configured and tested in parallel with the real machine to accelerate the commissioning process, reduce risks and decrease costs.&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;/ul&gt;
 &lt;div&gt;
 &lt;p&gt;Read this whitepaper to learn how early adopters are already benefiting from the power of the Digital Twin as part of their Industry 4.0 strategy.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
