&lt;p&gt;Hydraulics systems offer unrivalled power density, life cycle performance and durability. However, their efficiency and longevity depend on clean, uncontaminated oil. Even in newly built systems, this cannot be guaranteed.&lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;p&gt;Contamination caused by tiny particles can lead to malfunction and permanent damage, and accounts for over 80% of hydraulic systems breakdowns.&lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;p&gt;Bosch Rexroth demonstrates how new generation filtration media can protect hydraulic systems, reducing costs and total cost of ownership for manufacturers.&lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;p&gt;Contamination caused by tiny particles can lead to malfunction and permanent damage, and accounts for over 80% of hydraulic systems breakdowns.&lt;/p&gt;
 &lt;ul&gt;
 &lt;li&gt;Improve service life of hydraulic systems by using newly developed filter materials&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li&gt;Reduce operating costs through fewer filter changes&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li&gt;Prevent further damage caused by electrostatic discharge&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;/ul&gt;
